<refsect1>
<title>Signals</title>
<refsect2><title><anchor id="GtkCheckMenuItem-toggled"/>The &quot;toggled&quot; signal</title>
<programlisting><link linkend="void">void</link>        user_function                  (<link linkend="GtkCheckMenuItem">GtkCheckMenuItem</link> *checkmenuitem,
                                            <link linkend="gpointer">gpointer</link> user_data);</programlisting>
<para>
This signal is emitted when the state of the check box is changed.
</para>

<para>
A signal handler can examine the <structfield>active</structfield> 
field of the <link linkend="GtkCheckMenuItem-struct"><type>GtkCheckMenuItem-struct</type></link> struct to discover the new state.
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>checkmenuitem</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara>the object which received the signal.

</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><parameter>user_data</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara>user data set when the signal handler was connected.</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>
